  "body": "*Description*:\r\nWhile protobuf validation exists for things like [interval and timeout](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/84cacd2a5598f8b7d50fe0ccd3ef8a6deecfc2fc/api/envoy/api/v2/core/health_check.proto#L27) in cluster health checking configuration, there is [no check \r\nfor whether values passed in make sense](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/84cacd2a5598f8b7d50fe0ccd3ef8a6deecfc2fc/source/common/upstream/health_checker_base_impl.cc#L19). Setting the interval to something nonsensical like 0 makes the process spin in an error loop so would be a lot more straightforward to have envoy fail fast in cases like these.",
